cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper involves computer vision (CV) techniques for automatic colorization, as well as natural language processing (NLP) techniques for language conditioning. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes two different architectures for language-conditioned colorization, which involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as deep learning, so cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves manipulating descriptive color words in captions, which could be considered a multimedia (MM) aspect, so cs.MM is also a possible sub-category.
